  <Docs>
    <summary>Holds the arguments used to customize a typeface variant, such as collection index, color palette, and variable-font axis positions.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a lightweight ref struct that carries the parameters used to
create a customized variant of a typeface. Pass it to
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)> to obtain a new
`SKTypeface` that uses the requested collection index, color palette, and
variable-font axis positions.

Because `SKFontArguments` is a `ref struct` it cannot be stored on the heap or
boxed. Configure its properties and pass it directly to the relevant method.

## Examples

```csharp
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    CollectionIndex = 0,
    PaletteIndex = 1,
    VariationDesignPosition = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate[]
    {
        new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"), Value = 700f }
    }
};
using var variantTypeface = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
